Japanese audio manufacturer Aiwa Co. Ltd. said  Tuesday its consolidated pre-tax earnings more than doubled from a year  earlier to 9.8 billion yen (95 million dollars) in the year to March.
The subsidiary of consumer electronics giant Sony Corp. said the sharply  higher profit, up from 4.2 billion yen the previous year, was accompanied by a  19 percent increase in worldwide sales to 210 billion yen.
Aiwa forecast an even higher profit of 10.7 billion yen for the current  year on improved sales of 240 billion yen.
